{
  "stem": "1929.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 61.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She did not look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was a very modern woman for her time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a graduate of the Gymnasium, which was a-- like higher than the high school would be here, maybe second year of college.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She played the piano.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was very modern, because this was the age where the Jewish community, especially my family, was coming out into more modern attire and modern way of, of thinking and doing things.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were really indistinguishable from the rest of the population at that time, which was not true going back 40, 50 years when we lived in little villages.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the fact that I think all-- both my sisters and my brother were very active in the Zionist movement and the young Zionist organizations.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were the leaders there in our town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were assisting others to go to, to Palestine at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I don't know if it's true or not, but I think my oldest sister, Ronia, did want to move to Palestine but my father objected to her leaving.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He didn't think that the condition in, in Palestine would be suitable for her.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He just-- I don't know if it's true or not, but that's the story I've heard.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so dealing with my sister, Ronia, she also was one of the very few Jews that worked for the utility- local electric utility company.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was a-- according to my brother, that was a very prestigious job for a Jewish person to have, because Jews were not employed in government at the time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was married, I think about 1936, to a very nice young man.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Subsequently, I think he was one-- he was actually a policeman in the-- in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
